                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 15, 1919—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>242. For Lansing from Glass. Delayed answering your cable 137 of January 3, 1919
                    pending exchange of cables with President. I am sending Strauss to Europe almost
                    immediately for a short stay. He is familiar with my views and with Treasury
                    policies in determination of which he has taken an important part.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
